<helm_chart_security_guide>
<title>HELM CHART SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Helm chart security testing covers secret exposure, insecure default values, RBAC misconfigurations, template injection, and dependency vulnerabilities.</critical>

<scope>
- Secret exposure in Helm charts
- Insecure default values
- RBAC misconfigurations
- Template injection in Helm templates
- Tiller security (Helm v2)
- Chart repository security
- Dependency vulnerabilities
</scope>

<secret_exposure>
{% raw %}
# Secrets in values.yaml:
helm show values chart-name | grep -i password

# Secrets in templates:
grep -r "password\|secret\|token" charts/*/templates/

# Hardcoded secrets:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
data:
  password: cGFzc3dvcmQxMjM=  # base64 encoded, not encrypted
{% endraw %}
</secret_exposure>

<template_injection>
{% raw %}
# Helm template injection:
# If user input in template:
{{ .Values.userInput }}

# Can inject:
{{ .Values.userInput }}{{ .Release.Name }}{{ .Release.Namespace }}
{% endraw %}
</template_injection>

<remember>Helm security: Check for exposed secrets in values/templates, test RBAC permissions, validate template injection protection, scan dependencies for vulnerabilities.</remember>
</helm_chart_security_guide>
